						<summary>

						<p>On pillar No. 7 in the compound of the Taluk Office.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated Śaka • • • ., <hi rend="italic">Śrāvaṇa,</hi> śu. 15, lunar eclipse. Written in 12th century characters.</p>						

						<p>Mentions [Kēdāru] Peggaḍa, <hi rend="italic">sandhivigrahin</hi> (minister for war and peace) working under Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara (name lost) who seems to have gifted sheep for a lamp in the Bhīmēśvara temple.</p>						

						</summary>
